<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-7662] logs servlet should use pathspec of /*</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-7662</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The logs servlet in HttpServer should use a pathspec of /* instead of /.&lt;br/&gt;
      logContext.addServlet(AdminAuthorizedServlet.class, &quot;/*&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In making the changes for the yarn webapps (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAPREDUCE-2999&quot; title=&quot;hadoop.http.filter.initializers not working properly on yarn UI&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAPREDUCE-2999&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAPREDUCE-2999&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), I registered a webapp to use &quot;/&quot;.  This blocked the /logs servlet from working.  because both had a pathSpec of &quot;/&quot; and the guice filter seemed to take precendence.  Changing the pathspec of the logs servlet to /* fixes the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
